==English==

===Etymology===
French ''[[décadent]]'', from Latin ''[[decadentia]]'', compound of ''de-'' down and ''cadere'' to fall; relating to [[decay]].

===Adjective===
'''decadent'''
# Characterised by [[moral]] or [[cultural]] [[decline]].
# Luxuriously [[self-indulgent]].

====Related terms====
*[[decadence]] ''noun''
*[[decay]] ''noun'', ''verb''

